  "body": "**üßê Motivation** I have identified a potential optimization in the ERC721 `safeTransferFrom` function in the OpenZeppelin Contracts library. By making a small change in the function implementation, I saved 32 gas per transaction. I believe this improvement could be beneficial for library users seeking to optimize gas costs in their smart contracts.\r\n\r\n**üìù Details** I propose the following change in the `safeTransferFrom` function:\r\n\r\n_Current implementation:_\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\n\r\n`function safeTransferFrom(address from, address to, uint256 tokenId) public virtual override {\r\n    safeTransferFrom(from, to, tokenId, \"\");\r\n}` \r\n```\r\n_Proposed change:_\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\n\r\n`function safeTransferFrom(address from, address to, uint256 tokenId) public virtual override {\r\n    require(_isApprovedOrOwner(_msgSender(), tokenId), \"ERC721: caller is not token owner or approved\");\r\n    _safeTransfer(from, to, tokenId, \"\");\r\n}` \r\n```\r\n\r\nBy directly calling `require(_isApprovedOrOwner(_msgSender(), tokenId), \"ERC721: caller is not token owner or approved\")` and `_safeTransfer(from, to, tokenId, \"\")` instead of the public `safeTransferFrom(from, to, tokenId, \"\")`, we can save **32 gas** per transaction. This change maintains the original functionality while providing a gas optimization.\r\n\r\nThank you for your time and effort in maintaining this valuable library ‚ù§Ô∏è",
